properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 1 at 3:14PM PST until January 2 at 3:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North to northeast winds 15 to 30 mph with gusts to 45
mph expected.

* WHERE...Ventura County Valleys, Santa Monica Mountains, Santa
Clarita Valley and San Fernando Valley.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to 3 PM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds will be northerly Wednesday night,
then become northeasterly Thursday morning.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 PM PST THURSDAY
